ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: How much physical activity/exercise do you get compared to other kids your age? (By physical activity we mean lots of running around, playing sports, or generally being active)
Notes: 1=A lot less; 2=Less; 3=About the same amount; 4=More; 5=A lot more

ElementDescription: Describe the type of physical activity/exercise
How often do you do activity?
Notes: 1=Almost Never (Less than once/month); 2=Every now and then (2-3 times/month); 3=Several times a week (1-4 times/week); 4=Almost every day (5-7 times/week)

ElementDescription: How well have you been sleeping for the last week?
Notes: 1=Extremely poorly; 2=Poorly; 3=Moderately; 4=Well; 5=Extremely well
